"><![CDATA[<p>A new launch of satellite location(s) for the ASN Program is being reviewed and is not anticipated for 2011. No Distance Education opportunities are currently offered.</p>
<h3>Distance Learning</h3>
<p>Students in  satellite locations will attend nursing classes, labs, and clinical at designated facilities. From a distant classroom, students will join BYU-Idaho classrooms for live instruction through a video/web conferencing system.  Clinical hours are scheduled for Fridays and/or Saturdays. Generally, 12 clinical hours are required each week.</p>
<h3>Participation Requirements</h3>
<p>A cohort of students will be admitted. While preference will be given to qualified students from the satelite areas, all students who meet the following requirements may apply:</p>
<ul>
<li>Students must have over 48 college credits, which include completing all the <a href="x28706.xml">Alternate Track Prerequisites</a>.</li>
<li>Students must have completed all general education and/or foundations course work before starting the Nursing Program.</li>
<li>Students must be admitted first to BYU-Idaho and meet all university requirements.</li>
<li>International students do not qualify due to Visa regulations. (Please contact <a href="http://www.byui.edu/international/" target="_self">International Services</a> for details.)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Application Deadlines</h3>
<p>There are no currently scheduled satellite locations. For the latest information, contact <a href="http://web.byui.edu/directory/employees/OfficeHours.aspx?User=WILLIAMSBR" target="_self">Brent Williams</a> at (208) 496-1280.<span style="color: #000000; font-family: helvetica;"> </span></p>
